race.comment: LADY OLENNA (7) has contested four Highways from as many appearances this prep and has been competitive in all of them without winning. The pick of the runs was last start when she chimed in late but just missed in a busy finish over 1100m at Wyong. Handles soft ground and an extra 100m should suit. BARELLO (5) last appeared six weeks ago when he had to dig deep to just prevail in a BM58 over this distance at Murwillumbah. Has progressed nicely since joining the Jordan Lee yard and although this is his biggest test he looks up to the task. ISHIKARI (10) resumed with a close second as favourite over 1280m at Orange recently. Lightly raced mare who doesn't mind the sting out of the ground so she is a definite contender. ATHENA'S TREASURE (6) closed powerfully to collect her third win from just five starts in a BM58 at Port Macquarie last start. Deserves her chance at this level. ONYSPEED (12) has been so-so in two runs this prep but can improve with this step up in distance.
